Subject: [PATCH] patch 0882: Movers news-catalyst classifier expanded 7 -> 50+
 patterns
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

User audit (NGL Movers): RUBYMILLS was tagged "Peer-sympathy momentum"
but the news headline literally said "Approves Independent Director
Appointment in EOGM"; MARKSANS / ASTRAMICRO were "smallcap momentum"
while their own earnings hit the wire same day. Root cause: only 7
catalyst patterns existed, so most news fell through to generic Tier
3/4 inference.

Now classifyNewsCatalyst runs 50+ ordered patterns covering:

CORPORATE ACTIONS / M&A (most specific first):
  acquisition (with % stake + target company capture)
  stake sale, JV formation, demerger, merger scheme, open offer,
  preferential allotment, warrant conversion, QIP, rights issue,
  buyback, bonus issue, stock split, interim/special dividend

EARNINGS:
  guidance raised/cut (highest priority)
  Q[1-4] results / quarterly results / net profit jumps
  earnings preview (results expected this week)

PROMOTER / FLOW:
  promoter buy/sell, pledge release/add, block-deal buy/sell, OFS

GOVERNANCE / LEADERSHIP (the RUBYMILLS gap):
  independent director appointment (now caught)
  CEO/MD appointment + resignation
  CFO change, auditor change
  board meeting fund-raise (distinct from generic board meeting)

BUSINESS EVENTS:
  order win with Rs Cr amount capture
  PSU customer capture (BHEL/NTPC/HAL/BEL/DRDO/ISRO/Indian Railways)
  new contract / LoA, capacity commissioning, capex announcement,
  new product launch, patent grant, MoU signing

REGULATORY:
  USFDA approval + USFDA 483/observation (separated)
  CDSCO/DCGI, WHO-GMP/EU-GMP, SEBI action, RBI action

RATING (PATCH 0709 vocabulary):
  ICRA/CRISIL/CARE/India Ratings/Fitch/Moody/S&P/BWR/Brickwork/Acuite
  upgrade vs downgrade vs outlook revision

INDEX / F&O:
  Nifty/Sensex/MSCI/FTSE inclusion + removal, F&O inclusion + ban

Plus GENERIC_NEWS clickbait filter: "Is Now The Time To Put X On Your
Watchlist", "Stock To Watch Today", "Here Is Why X Is Up" — these
fall through to Tier 3/4 inference rather than masquerading as
catalysts (CORDSCABLE pattern).

Labels now extract specifics where possible: "acquires 74% stake in
TargetCo", "bagged Rs 250 Cr order from BHEL", "credit rating upgrade",
"independent director appointment" - not generic "M&A" / "News
mention" buckets.
